Sure, here's a simple example of an HTML landing page:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Simple Landing Page</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 50px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #fff;
            box-shadow: 0px 0px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }
        h1 {
            font-size: 2.5em;
            margin-top: 0;
        }
        p {
            font-size: 1.1em;
            line-height: 1.5;
        }
        .cta-button {
            display: inline-block;
            margin-top: 20px;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: #fff;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
        }
        .cta-button:hover {
            background-color: #3e8e41;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Welcome to Our Simple Landing Page</h1>
        <p>This is a basic example of an HTML landing page, with a clean and simple design. It includes a container with some text and a call-to-action button.</p>
        <p>Feel free to use this template as a starting point for your own landing page, and customize it to fit your needs.</p>
        <a class="cta-button" href="#">Learn More</a>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
```
This code includes a basic HTML structure, some CSS for styling, and a container with a heading, some text, and a call-to-action button. You can customize the text, colors, and other elements to fit your needs.
